    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced chorizo</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until crispy</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-haddock-chorizo-and-sweetcorn-chowder/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and dice</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-haddock-chorizo-and-sweetcorn-chowder/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chorizo is crispy, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>, <strong>diced pepper</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> (skin on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[330ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[330ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>\u2013\u00a0this is your<strong> creamy stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-haddock-chorizo-and-sweetcorn-chowder/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the red onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped sweet potato</strong>,\u00a0<strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ground cumin </strong>and <strong>cornflour </strong>to the pan</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>creamy stock </strong>and cook for 10-12 min over a medium heat or until slightly thickened</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-haddock-chorizo-and-sweetcorn-chowder/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the sweet potato is cooking, drain your <strong>sweetcorn</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-haddock-chorizo-and-sweetcorn-chowder/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once slightly thickened, add your <strong>haddock bites</strong> (unevenly sized haddock bites? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!) to the pan and cook, covered for a further 10-15 min or until the sweet potato is tender and the haddock is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in half and add to a<strong> toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-haddock-chorizo-and-sweetcorn-chowder/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the haddock is cooked, add the <strong>drained sweetcorn </strong>with the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime[s]</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>\u00a0(save the rest for garnish) to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>Mexican-style haddock, chorizo & sweetcorn chowder</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-haddock-chorizo-and-sweetcorn-chowder/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Mexican-style haddock, chorizo & sweetcorn chowder</strong> with the <strong>toasted ciabatta </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining chopped coriander</strong> and a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
